Param.name: Event_ID
Param.Description: Trigger ID

Param.Description: Type of the alert

Group.name: Status

Param.name: Event_status
Param.Description: Event status (preliminary, initial, update, retractation)

Param.name: Iteration
Param.Description: Iteration Number

Param.name: Event_inst
Param.Description: Instrument which originated the alert

Param.name: Loc_url
Param.Description: The url location of healpix skymap

Param.name: FA
Param.Description: GRANDMA follow-up advocate on duty at the time of the VO alert

Param.name: Retraction
Param.Description: Set to 1 if the event is retracted.

Param.name: HardwareInj
Param.Description: Indicates that this event is a hardware injection if 1, no if 0

Param.name: Event_page
Param.Description: Web page for evolving status of this GW candidate

Param.name: FAR
Param.Description: Web page for evolving status of this GW candidate

Param.name: Group
Param.Description: Low-latency data analysis pipeline

Group.name: Classification

Param.name: BNS
Param.Description: Probability that the source is a binary neutron star merger

Param.name: NSBH
Param.Description: Probability that the source is a neutron star - black hole merger

Param.name: BBH
Param.Description: Probability that the source is a binary black hole merger

Param.name: Terrestrial
Param.Description: Probability that the source is terrestrial (i.e., a background noise fluctuation or a glitch)

Group.Description: Source classification: binary neutron star (BNS), neutron star-black hole (NSBH), binary black hole (BBH), or terrestrial (noise)

Group.name: Properties

Param.name: HasNS
Param.Description: Probability that at least one object in the binary has a mass that is less than 3 solar masses

Param.name: HasRemnant
Param.Description: Probability that a nonzero mass was ejected outside the central remnant object

Group.Description: Qualitative properties of the source, conditioned on the assumption that the signal is an astrophysical compact binary merger

Param.Description: FOV of the telescope used for the observation strategy

Param.Description: Shape of the FOV for the telescope used for the observation strategy

Param.Description: Magnitude limit of the telescope used for the observation strategy

Param.name: exposuretime
Param.Description: Exposure time of the telescope used for the observation strategy

Param.name: Slew_rate
Param.Description: Slew rate of the telescope for the observation strategy

Param.name: Readout
Param.Description: Read out of the telescope used for the observation strategy

Param.name: Filters
Param.Description: Filters of the telescope used for the observation strategy

Param.name: Latitude

Param.Description: Longitude of the observatory

Param.Description: Elevation of the observatory

Param.Description: Set to 1 if observation are required, 0 to stop the observations
